================
README
================

ServerOnDuty
======================

ServerOnDuty is distributed Continuous Integration System. It focus on running integrations from large projects on LAN.

It is still on its early phase of development and NOT ready for general use.

Developers / contributors
==========================

(in chronological order)

 * Eduardo Schettino - schettino72 at gmail dot com
 * Kevin - ?
 * Balazs - ?
 * Edward -?

Development was partially sponsored by Exoweb (march & april 2010)

Project Details
===============

 - Website http://code.google.com/p/serveronduty/


INSTALL
=======

ServerOnDuty should on python 2.5, 2.6.

``python setup.py install``


DEPENDENCIES
============

- werkzeug (0.6)
- SQLAlchemy (0.5.8)
- Mako (0.3.1)
- PyYaml (3.09)
- CherryPy (3.1.2)
- doit (0.6)
- simplejson

Tools required for development:

- py.test * unit-tests
- mock * unit-tests
- mercurial * VCS
- pyflakes * syntax checker



TESTS
=====

* sodd::
 $ py.test


DOCUMENTATION
=============

http://code.google.com/p/serveronduty/


FAQ
=====

How to remove calculated integration results ?
------------------------------------------------

::

 delete from integration_result;


